Description:
Dark Chocolate Fudge
(Gluten Free, Vegan)

375gms dark chocolate broken in to pieces
395g can sweeten  condensed milk
1/2 cup icing sugar sifted
1/2 cup glace red cherries chopped
1/2 cup dried cranberries chopped
3/4 cup pistachios chopped
extra cranberries and chopped pistachios chopped for garnish

Grease a loaf tin and line with foil then grease the foil also.  Melt the chocolate in a bowl over a pan of boiling water.  Once completely melted add sugar then condensed milk.  Mix in the rest of the ingredients, except garnish and pour into prepared tin.  Smooth top and add garnish, then gently push into but not completely.  Refrigerate over night and cut into small squares or slices.  You can easily replace the cherries, cranberries and pistachios with other dried fruit or nuts!

Apple Pie with a twist

If you hate rolling pastry, but love home made style, this is a good one for you!

150 gms butter
2/3 cup sugar
1 large egg
2 1/2 cups flour s
1/3-1/2 cup milk
Pinch of salt
Tin of ready apple pie filling ( if you want to cheat)

Cream sugar and butter, then add egg. Add flour and salt, then milk 1/3 cup first then if it seems dry add the rest to make up to 1/2 cup. Divide in two and roll into balls and wrap in glad wrap and refrigerate for at least an hour. Prepare dish by greasing with a little butter and use your hands to push one ball into the dish to make the base. Pour in apple and make flat with the back of a spoon. Grate the other ball until all used up and top completely covered. Cook in slow oven for one hour. Serve with ice cream and/or cream. Great hot or cold!

American Style BBQ Spare Ribs

1.8 kg Pork Spare Ribs
6 tbsp tomatoe sauce
3 tbsp honey
2 tbsp red wine vinegar
2 tbsp mustard
S and P to taste

Cut ribs then boil in large pot for 20 minutes and drain well. Mix all other ingredients in a small bowl and set aside. Place meat and marinate in large marinating container.  Ensure all meat is covered. Leave overnight, but turn occasionally.  Cook on BBQ and serve with corn on the cob and Spanish rice.

Simple Fried Rice

4-6 cups cooked rice
300-400gms diced bacon
3 corn cobs corn removed 
3 spring onions chopped 
2-3 tbsp sesame oil
Soy sauce to taste
SandP to taste (white pepper)

Heat oil in large fry pan and add diced bacon. Cook until bacon starting to brown, then add corn. Stir corn until all coat and mixed with bacon and cook a few more minutes. Add rice and cook until heated through, add soy sauce and spring onions and stir until mixed in.  Easy and yummy! Make gluten free by using gluten free soy sauce.

Calzone
(Vegetarian)

200-300gms pizza dough
90-100 gms Tapenade
200 gms grated cheese
Olive oil
Flour

Heat oven to 180 degrees and spray baking tray with olive oil, set aside. Flour bench and roll out dough to a big oval and till the dough is approximately 2-3 mm thick.  Spread tapenade along the middle and sprinkle cheese on top of tapenade. Paint a little olive oil on the edges and bring the long edges together in the middle and squeeze them together and fold them over as you move along the length. It should look like a pasty with no gaps or else your contents will leak out. Carefully lift onto tray and paint entire surface generously with olive oil. Bake for 20-30 mins until golden brown. Cut in slices and serve hot or cold. Make two at a time because it gets eaten very quickly 😀

Quick and Easy Dessert

1 banana per person 
1/4 Lemon
1 Tbsp butter
1 Tbsp honey
Cinnamon 
Cream

Chop banana on diagonal, melt butter in fry pan on medium heat, add bananas.  Squeeze lemon in pan and add honey and stir continuously, but gently and flip bananas over occasionally.  Cook until the banana is soft but not falling apart. Pour into a bowl and serve with cream and cinnamon sprinkled on top- delish!

Easy Vegetable Lentil Curry

2 Tbsp oil
4 Tbsp green curry paste
2-4 garlic cloves crushed 
200gm butternut and regular pumpkin chopped
1 sweet potatoe peeled and chopped
1-2 carrots chopped
2 cups red lentils
4 stock cubes
100 gms frozen spinach
4-6 cups of water (add 6 cups if you like it more runny or less if you prefer it more solid- I add one stock cube per cup)

Heat oil in a large pot and cook garlic for 2 minutes then add curry paste and cook for a further 2-3 mins.  Add all other ingredients except spinach and cook until veggies are soft, about 20-40 mins.  Add spinach and stir until completely mixed through.  Serve with rice, yogurt and coriander sprinkled on top- Top Notch!

Simple Dahl served with ancient grains and coriander 

1 cup yellow split peas
3 cups water or vegetable stock 
4-6 garlic cloves chopped
4 inches ginger grated
1 teaspoon cumin
1/2 teaspoon coriander
1/2 teaspoon turmeric
1/2 teaspoon Garam masala
1/2 teaspoon chilli
Salt to taste
Olive oil
Root veggies you have in your fridge chopped and frozen spinach

Soak split peas over night then put on higher heat and bring to the boil.  Cook for 20 minutes. Mean while heat some olive oil in a small fry pan and cook garlic then ginger for 3-5 mins add the spices and cook a further 2 minutes. Add a little water to the pan and add to split peas.  Add all the veggies and cook until veggies are soft (about 30-40 mins.) Add spinach and stir until completely mixed through. Serve with ancient grains and coriander sprinkled on top.
